rdf:Description.lla:note: Luois Dermonth has been discharged and left behind at this port having been convicted for assaulting John Williams and condemned to 15 days imprisonment and wages due to him have been paid to British Consulate in cash and his effects delivered to him in the Consular prison 23rdMay 1878
David Pugh was discharged and left behind at the port of Barletta on the alleged grounds of having consumption
James Ross has been reported as having died, to The British Consulate, Lisbon on February 7th 1879 by the Master. He died by falling from aloft on 31st December 1878.
